arded as not open to new ideas\n- Sometimes not good at taking criticism\n- Can be unorganized\nThere is **no direct information** on A\u2019s communication style (e.g., briefing quality, listening skills) or documented crew\u2011lead/teamwork experience beyond the general leadership quality. The notes about difficulty taking criticism and being a show\u2011off hint at possible interpersonal friction, but they do not provide concrete evidence of how A works within a crew.\n**Current assessment**\nAll four candidates still present a mix of strong technical/reliability traits and notable interpersonal weaknesses, and the missing concrete evidence on crew\u2011lead, communication style, and teamwork for A, B, C, and D prevents a confident ranking. Therefore, I remain **Undecided** about which candidate best satisfies the full set of long\u2011distance pilot criteria.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Undecided\"}", "thoughts": "We need to act as agent_2. We have internal memory and we have seen the latest discussion: Agent 3 posted a public message summarizing and asking for missing info about D, B, A. Agent 2 now must respond. We have tool access to agent_1_tool and agent_3_tool. We can ask for missing info. We have some info about candidates from earlier. We can answer any questions asked to us. The latest public message from Agent 3 includes three questions:\n\n1. Candidate D: any observations of his communication style or concrete examples of teamwork/crew-lead performance?\n2. Candidate B: any specific feedback or incidents that illustrate how his \u201cwrong tone\u201d or pretentiousness has impacted crew coordination?\n3. Candidate A: any known examples of his communication approach and past crew-cooperation?\n\nWe as agent_2 need to answer these if we have info. Let's check our internal memory: we have the list of facts. For D: we have \"responds to unexpected events adequately\", \"can concentrate very well\", \"solves problems extremely well\", \"takes responsibility seriously\", \"regarded as a know-it-all\", \"has a hot temper\", \"regarded as arrogant\", \"relatively weak leadership skills\". No explicit communication style. So we can answer: no explicit info on communication style, but we have some hints: hot temper, arrogant, know-it-all may affect communication. But we must not infer beyond given facts. We can state we have no direct info on communication style or teamwork, only the listed attributes.\n\nFor B: we have \"very conscientious\", \"handles stress very well\", \"good at assessing weather conditions\", \"excellent computer skills\", \"relatively weak memory for numbers\", \"makes nasty remarks about his colleagues\", \"sometimes adopts the wrong tone when communicating\", \"regarded as pretentious\". So we can answer that we have no specific incidents, but we have these attributes indicating potential impact.\n\nFor A: we have \"can anticipate dangerous situations\", \"able to see complex connections\", \"excellent spatial vision\", \"very good leadership qualities\", \"regarded as a show-off\", \"regarded as being not open to new ideas\", \"sometimes not good at taking criticism\", \"can be unorganized\". No explicit communication style. So we can answer we have no direct info on communication approach, but we have these attributes.\n\nThus we can answer the three questions with the info we have.\n\nWe also need to provide our current assessment and vote. We remain Undecided.\n\nWe must output PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON.\n\nProceed."}
